    "Distributional Q-learning learns a categorical distribution of discounted returns instead of estimating the mean.",
    "Noisy DQN uses stochastic network layers for exploration.",
    "Given this, Hessel et al. (2018) investigated how to combine these different but complementary ideas, using ER, into an ensemble approach called Rainbow, which achieved state-of-the-art on 57 Atari 2600 games in ALE (Bellemare et al. 2013) concerning data efficiency and final performance.",
